A King Charles Spaniel suffered three degree burns from a pad used to keep him warm during a scan which vets had heated up in a microwave .
Twelve-year-old Alfie underwent a general anaesthetic for an MRI scan at the Animal Health Trust clinic in Newmarket , Suffolk .
The pet is also completely deaf had the scan got too hot and found puss oozing from his back .
Alfie is calling on all vets to heat up the pads .